# ION DEX UI Code Spec

## 1. Exact Color Palette (Tailwind config)

```css
/* tailwind.config.ts extend.colors — use these, nothing else */
ion: {
  bg:       '#0a0a1a',  /* deepest navy */
  surface:  '#0f0f2a',  /* card base */
  glass:    'rgba(15,15,42,0.55)', /* glassmorphism fill */
  cyan:     '#00e5ff',  /* primary neon */
  magenta:  '#e040fb',  /* secondary neon */
  violet:   '#b388ff',  /* tertiary neon */
  gold:     '#ffd740',  /* accent */
  green:    '#69f0ae',  /* success */
  red:      '#ff5252',  /* danger */
  border:   'rgba(0,229,255,0.25)', /* neon border base */
  'border-strong': 'rgba(0,229,255,0.6)', /* thick neon rim */
  text:     '#e0e0ff',  /* body */
  'text-dim': '#8080b0', /* secondary */
}
```

## 2. Glass Card Spec (MANDATORY)

Every card/panel MUST use this structure, NOT a plain `<div>`:

```tsx
<div className="relative rounded-2xl p-[2px] overflow-hidden
  bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500/30 via-violet-500/20 to-magenta-500/30
  shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(0,229,255,0.15),0_0_60px_rgba(224,64,251,0.1)]">
  {/* Glass surface */}
  <div className="absolute inset-[2px] rounded-2xl bg-[#0f0f2a]/80 backdrop-blur-2xl z-0" />
  {/* Content */}
  <div className="relative z-10 p-6">
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
```

Key rules:
- Border gradient: cyan → violet → magenta, 0.3/0.2/0.3 opacity
- Outer glow shadow: cyan 30px + magenta 60px
- Glass backdrop: `backdrop-blur-2xl` + `bg-[#0f0f2a]/80`
- Border radius: `rounded-2xl` for cards, `rounded-3xl` for hero
- Padding: `p-6` default, `p-4` for small inner panels

## 3. Hero Card Spec (feature cards on dashboard)

Hero cards MUST be thicker neon rim (2px pseudo-border via padding trick above, or dedicated thick border):

```tsx
<div className="relative rounded-3xl p-[3px] overflow-hidden
  bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-400/60 via-violet-400/40 to-magenta-400/60
  shadow-[0_0_40px_rgba(0,229,255,0.25),0_0_80px_rgba(224,64,251,0.15)]
  hover:shadow-[0_0_60px_rgba(0,229,255,0.4),0_0_100px_rgba(224,64,251,0.25)]
  transition-shadow duration-500">
  <div className="relative rounded-[22px] bg-[#0a0a1a]/90 backdrop-blur-3xl p-6 z-10">
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
```

## 4. NeonButton Spec

```tsx
<button className="relative px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-semibold text-sm
  bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-500/20 to-violet-500/20
  border border-cyan-400/40
  text-cyan-300
  shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(0,229,255,0.2)]
  hover:from-cyan-500/40 hover:to-violet-500/40
  hover:border-cyan-400/60
  hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(0,229,255,0.4)]
  transition-all duration-300">
  {children}
</button>
```

## 5. Text Typography

```
Headings: font-bold tracking-wide text-white
- h1: text-3xl md:text-4xl
- h2: text-2xl md:text-3xl
- h3: text-xl

Body: font-normal text-ion-text (e0e0ff)
- text-sm for secondary info
- text-xs for labels

Numbers: font-mono tabular-nums
- Price: text-2xl md:text-3xl text-cyan-300
- Amount: text-lg text-white
- Change %: text-sm, green=pos red=neg

NEVER use: text-gray-*, text-slate-*, font-serif, plain white bg
```

## 6. Background Layer

AuroraGalaxyBackground must be FULL VIEWPORT, z-0, always visible behind all content:

```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 z-0">
  <AuroraGalaxyBackground />
</div>
<div className="relative z-10 min-h-screen">
  {/* App content */}
</div>
```

The background must use SVG/Canvas with:
- Deep navy base `#0a0a1a`
- Aurora waves: cyan → violet → magenta gradients, moving slowly
- Starfield: 200+ small white dots, opacity 0.3-0.7, parallax on scroll
- Galaxy nebula: large blurred circles in cyan/magenta, very low opacity

## 7. Data Rules (RED LINE)

- NO `mockPreviewMeta` imports in page files
- NO `GlassPlaceholderSkeleton` in production pages
- NO `MOCK_DATA` imports
- NO hardcoded numbers like `$1.23`, `100 ION`
- Every displayed value MUST come from: ionApi.ts hooks, usePreviewResource, ion-indexer-cache, or real wallet context
- Loading state = `<AsyncState resource={...}>` wrapping real API call
- Error state = `<AsyncState>` with retry button

## 8. Responsive Breakpoints

```
Mobile:  375px  → single column, compact cards, hamburger nav
Tablet:  768px  → 2-column grid, bottom nav optional
Desktop: 1440px → full trading layout, sidebar nav, multi-column
```

Use Tailwind: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3`

## 9. BusinessPages.tsx SPLIT REQUIREMENT

The 43KB BusinessPages.tsx MUST be split into separate page files:
- `pages/TradePage.tsx` — chart + order book + order form
- `pages/GridPage.tsx` — grid trading config
- `pages/BurnPage.tsx` — ION burn interface
- `pages/DomainPage.tsx` — .ion domain management
- `pages/AIPage.tsx` — AI analysis panel

Keep shared layouts in `components/layout/`, shared primitives in `components/ui/`.

## 10. Verification After Every Change

```bash
node scripts/dev-preflight.mjs
npm run build          # MUST pass
npm run typecheck      # if available
npm run verify         # Playwright E2E
npm run audit:high     # 0 high vulnerabilities
powershell scripts\check-encoding.ps1  # UTF-8 check
```

DO NOT commit if any of these fail.
